        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 26 at 1:57PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 156 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms in southeastern Siskiyou and southweastern Modoc
counties, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lava Lake Campground, Day, Lookout, and Adin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
